<title type="html"><![CDATA[interlacing]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=3337&amp;p=23869#p23869"><![CDATA[
The 32X <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Genlock" class="postlink">genlocked</a> its own video to that of the Genesis. (Evidence: Some 32X games used the Genesis PPU for the backgrounds and the 32X PPU for sprites.) Perhaps if the Genesis PPU was in 480i mode, the 32X would offset every other field down by a half scanline, giving the effect you seek.<br /><br />But the NES, on the other hand, can't genlock to any 480i source.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Tue May 01, 2007 11:46 am</p><hr />
